The Commission of Inquiry into State Capture will on Thursday continue to hear evidence relating to allegations of corruption at the Free State government. Expected to testify are Director of the ORI Group Abel Kgotso Manyike, SMD Trading owner Shaun Duminy and former Director General of Department of Human Settlements, Thabane Wiseman Zulu. Their testimony relates to a R255-millon tender to eradicate asbestos roofs from low cost homes in the province. Live proceedings will be streamed in the video below:  